vectorData.altText: 11. Identify the class of tissue. Be specific.
Thats right! Areolar CT can be identified by the variety of cell and fibre types. In addition, GS occupies a large volume of the tissue, as represented by the white space.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

This is a section of loose (areolar) connective tissue from a mesentery, in which we can see type I collagen fibres (abundant, wavy fibres that stain pink/red) and elastic fibres (finer, straighter, black, scattered). The seemingly empty spaces are filled with ground substance, in life.
